The Russians have warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters has increased, which replace the bank’s phone number.
This is reported by Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator transmitted information to the operators about more than 2,5 thousand numbers, from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, the operators discovered the replacement of the number.
A further 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases, restrictions on the use of financial services were imposed.
The deputy head of the information security department of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that the replacement of the number faced a wide range of Russian banks.
He explained that the operators do not always respond to the Central Bank’s warnings about fraudulent calls, referring to the absence of such a duty in the Law on Communications.
In the bank "Opening", Rosbank and Alfa-bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the replacement of the number.
As reported in the press service "Bilaina", part of the information about fraudulent calls that the Central Bank transmitted was incorrect: the lists got numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to disruptions in the organization’s work.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of numbers of fraudsters, to which the operator of the communication will contact at each call to check the number.
He explained that it would be necessary to amend the legislation to create such a base.
