The supply of “sanctions” to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries that fell under the Russian food embargo has decreased more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to the President of the Russian Federation Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from the sanctions countries versus 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period of 2013, reports Interfax.
At the same time, the value of imported products decreased to $226.5 million from $4 billion to 975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about deliveries of goods that did not fall under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the lapsed volumes of the prohibited products were compensated by the increase in imports from CIS countries, Africa, South-East Asia, Serbia.
Recall that at the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited from importing into Russia as part of counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official legal information portal, noted that the rules have been extended for another one per year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the effect of the decree on the destruction of the sanction was extended to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, since August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein have "attached" to this list, since January 1, 2016 - Ukraine.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products that fell under the food embargo, which Moscow introduced in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government has allowed the destruction of “sanctional” food in any lawful way.
As Western sanctions are maintained, the Russian Federation has also extended its response measures.
At the same time, on products that citizens import for personal use, this measure does not apply.
The ban does not apply to imports of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation for the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov previously called it “just immoral” destruction of food products, and this, he said, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, with the initiative to ban the destruction of food products suitable for use, Rospotrebnadzor spoke in early June.
After that, a similar recommendation was made to the government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister of Russia Alexey Gordeev said that destroying food products is wrong, and you need to think about how to use them on purpose, evaluating the quality.
The head of the company is found guilty in the avoidance of tax payments
the judgment of the Lenin District Court of Cheboksary. the director of the company "Land and Law" Vyacheslav Morozov pleaded guilty to the crimes provided for in paragraph "b" of article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (absence from payment of taxes with the organization by way of tax deduction)
This is reported by the press service of the Investigative Directorate of the SCR in Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov included in the tax records of LLC information about incomplete transactions.
According to fictitious documents, the company carried additional costs, and consequently, the amount of taxes to be paid for the added value and profit of the organization was reduced by 11.2 million rubles.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will be opened in the center of the capital
A new school will be opened in Hamovnik.
