In Chile began to build a telescope worth <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>1 billion
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
According to ESO, this week officially began the construction of a dome of the building, where the European Extremely Large Telescope (E-ELT) will be located, the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project so far.
Its total value, according to ESO, will exceed one billion euros.
Much of this money will be spent on the manufacture of equipment and construction of the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-sized mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be collected from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two supporting reflecting surfaces in diameters of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT get the first detailed photos of planets outside the Solar System, stars in other galaxies, as well as search for Earth's doppelgangers.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory for observations around Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome is only started, mirrors, scientific tools and other components of the observatory, scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, the total cost of which was about 400 million euros, was received by the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
